1930}}\n*[[Venezuelan Air Force]] received 15 T.52s.\n\n==Aircraft on display==\n[[File:jet.provost.t3a.xm479.arp.jpg|thumb|ex-RAF BAC Jet Provost T3A in private ownership]]\n* Jet Provost T4, ''XS209'', is located at the [[Solway Aviation Museum]], [[Carlisle Lake District Airport]], England.<ref>[http://www.solway-aviation-museum.co.uk/?page_id=105 \"Aircraft.\"] ''Solway Aviation Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T4, 'XS186' is preserved in ground runnable condition at the Metheringham Airfield Visitor Centre in Lincolnshire, England.  \n* Jet Provost T5, ''XW287'', (the 1st T5 off the line) is located at the Sulphur Springs, Texas Airport. USA\n* Jet Provost T5, ''XW323'', is located at the [[Royal Air Force Museum London]], [[Hendon Aerodrome]], [[London]], England.<ref name = \"rafmus\">[http://www.rafmuseum.org.uk/research/collections/british-aircraft-corporation-jet-provost-t5a/ \"British Aircraft Corporation Jet Provost T5A.\"] ''RAF Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T4, ''XP627'', is on display at [[North East Aircraft Museum]], [[Sunderland, Tyne and Wear|Sunderland]], [[Tyne and Wear]], England.<ref>[http://www.nelsam.org.uk/NEAM/Exhibits/History/XP627.htm \"BAC Jet Provost T.4 (XP627).\"] ''North East Aircraft Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T3A, ''XN586'', is on display at the [[Brooklands Museum]], [[Weybridge]], [[Surrey]], England.<ref>[http://www.brooklandsmuseum.com/index.php?/explore/aircraft-gliders-cockpit-sections/ \"Powered Aircraft, Gliders & Aircraft Cockpit Sections.\"] ''Brooklands Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* A Jet Provost T4 is preserved at the [[Yorkshire Air Museum]], [[Elvington, City of York|Elvington]], [[York]], England.<ref>[http://yorkshireairmuseum.org/exhibits/cold-war-aircraft/hunting-percival-jet-provost-t4/ \"Hunting Percival Jet Provost T.4.\"] ''Yorkshire Air Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T4, ''XP557'', is at [[Dumfries and Galloway Aviation Museum]], [[Dumfries]], Scotland.<ref>[http://www.dumfriesaviationmuseum.com/jet-provost \"Jet Provost T4 XP557.\"] ''Dumfries and Galloway Aviation Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T4 ''XP568'' is on static display at East Midlands Aeropark.<ref>[http://www.eastmidlandsairport.com/at-the-airport/attractions/the-aeropark/aircraft-on-display/ \"Aircraft on Display.\"] ''East Midlands Airport'', Retrieved: 29 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T3A, ''XM412'', is located on the airfield at [[Balado, Kinross|Balado]], near [[Kinross]], Scotland.<ref>[https://www.flickr.com/photos/egbj/14498973858 \"Jet Provost T3A XM412.\"] ''Flickr'', Retrieved: 6 March 2017.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T3A, ''XM414'', is located at [[RAF Langford Lodge]], [[Belfast]], [[Northern Ireland]].<ref>[http://www.ulsteraviationsociety.org/jet-provost/4535716887 \"Jet Provost T3A XM414.\"] ''Ulster Aviation Society'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T3A, ''XM464'', is on static display at [[Pima Air & Space Museum]] in [[Tucson, Arizona]].<ref>[http://www.pimaair.org/aircraft-by-name/item/hunting-t-3a-jet-provost \"Jet Provost T3A XM464.\"] ''Pima Air & Space Museum'', Retrieved: 16 February 2019.</ref>\n* The only Jet Provost T2 to enter service with the RAAF, ''A99-1'', is preserved at the [[RAAF Museum]], [[RAAF Williams]], [[Point Cook, Victoria|Point Cook]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia.<ref name = \"prov raaf\">[https://www.airforce.gov.au/raafmuseum/research/aircraft/series2/A99.htm \"A99 Jet Provost.\"] ''RAAF Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T4, ''XR679 (C-FDJP)'', is housed at the [[Jet Aircraft Museum]], [[London International Airport]], [[Ontario]], Canada.<ref name=\"XR679 cana\">[http://www.jetaircraftmuseum.ca/index.php/our-aircraft/11-our-aircraft/36-bac-jet-provost \"BAC Jet Provost.\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706084628/http://www.jetaircraftmuseum.ca/index.php/our-aircraft/11-our-aircraft/36-bac-jet-provost |date=6 July 2016 }} ''Jet Aircraft Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T5A, ''XW357'', is on display at the [[National Transport and Toy Museum, Wanaka|National Transport and Toy Museum]], [[Wanaka]], New Zealand.<ref>[http://nttmuseumwanaka.co.nz/bac-jet-provost-t5a/ \"BAC Jet Provost T5A.\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160122061722/http://nttmuseumwanaka.co.nz/bac-jet-provost-t5a/ |date=22 January 2016 }} ''National Transport & Toy Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* Jet Provost T5A, ''XW405'', is on display at the [[Hartlepool College of Further Education]], [[Hartlepool]], England.<ref>[https://c2.staticflickr.com/4/3745/12861686594_fa8219d5de_b.jpg] ''Hartlepool College of Further Education'', Retrieved: 9 August 2016.</ref>\n* A Jet Provost T3A is housed at the [[Tillamook Air Museum]], [[Oregon]], United States.<ref>[http://www.tillamookair.com/aircraft/ \"Aircraft.\"] ''Tillamook Air Museum'', Retrieved: 21 April 2016.</ref>\n* 2 Jet Provost T51s are on display at the [[Sri Lanka Air Force Museum]], Rathmalana, Sri Lanka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.airforcemuseum.lk|title=Sri Lanka Air Force Museum|website=www.airforcemuseum.lk|access-date=2018-05-22}}</ref>\n* Jet Provost T3 ''XN458'' was bought on [[eBay]] for \u00a31,050 by a group of people formed for the purpose, the 458 Club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.crakehal.demon.co.uk/XN458/XN458_Index.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211135602/http://www.crakehal.demon.co.uk/XN458/XN458_Index.htm|archive-date=11 February 2012|website=458 Club|title=XN458}}</ref> It was put on display after restoration, in the original 1960s colour scheme of [[No. 1 Flying Training School RAF|1 FTS]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.airport-data.com/aircraft/XN458.html |title=Aircraft Data XN458, 1960 Hunting P-84 Jet Provost T.3 C/N PAC/W/10137 |website=Airport-data.com |date=  |author= |accessdate= 10 August 2018}}</ref> in the [[beer garden]] of the Standard Inn, [[Northallerton]], [[North Yorkshire]], England, whose [[Landlord#Licensed victualler|landlord]] Paul Greig found and [[Auction sniping|snipe]]-bid for the aircraft.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/uk-england-york-north-yorkshire-45146371/jet-provost-lands-in-yorkshire-pub-beer-garden |title=Jet Provost lands in Yorkshire pub beer garden|website=BBC News|author= |date= 10 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.harrogateadvertiser.co.uk/news/vintage-jet-in-beer-garden-1-2625596 |title=Vintage jet in beer garden!|website=Harrogate Advertiser |date=26 May 2005 |author= |accessdate= 10 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Specifications (T Mk. 5) ==\n[[File:BAC Jet Provost T4 XP673 03 (G-RAFI) (7211694114).jpg|thumb|Open cockpit and nose cone of a Jet Provost]]\n[[File:XW420 (8999744158).jpg|thumb|Head-on view of a BAC Jet Provost]]\n{{aircraft specifications\n<!-- if you do not understand how to use this template, please ask at [[Wikipedia talk:WikiProject Aircraft]] -->\n\n<!-- please answer the following questions -->\n|plane or copter?=plane\n|jet or prop?=jet\n\n<!-- Now, fill out the specs. Please include units where appropriate (main comes first, alt in parentheses). If an item doesn't apply, like capacity, leave it blank. For additional lines, end your alt units with a right parenthesis \")\" and start a new, fully-formatted line beginning with an asterisk \"*\" -->\n|ref=Jane's All The World's Aircraft 1971\u201372,<ref name=\"Janes 71 p181\">Taylor 1971, p. 181.</ref> Flight International,<ref name=\"fi55 p585\">''Flight International'', 6 May 1955, p. 585.</ref> BAE Systems<ref name=\"herit prov\">[http://www.baesystems.com/en-uk/heritage/jet-provost-strikemaster \"Heritage \u2013 Product \u2013 Jet Provost.\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160508062251/http://www.baesystems.com/en-uk/heritage/jet-provost-strikemaster |date=8 May 2016 }} ''BAE Systems'', Ret