nadair CT-114 Tutor]]\n*[[HAL Kiran]]\n* [[Cessna T-37 Tweet]]\n* [[Fouga CM.170 Magister]]\n* [[Saab 105]]\n|lists=\n* [[List of aircraft of the Royal Air Force]]\n|see also=\n* [[Red Pelicans]]\n}}\n\n== References ==\n\n===Citations===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n{{refbegin}}\n* Clarke, Bob. ''Jet Provost: The Little Plane With The Big History''. Stroud, UK: Amberley Publishing Plc, 2008. {{ISBN|978-1-84868-097-5}}.\n* [http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1958/1958%20-%200779.html \"Jet Provost T.3\"]. ''[[Flight International]]'', 13 June 1958. Vol. 73, No. 2577, pp.&nbsp;795\u2013799.\n* [http://www.flightglobal.com/pdfarchive/view/1955/1955%20-%200582.html \"Jet Provost: Hunting Percival's New Ab Initio Trainer.\"] ''Flight International'', 6 May 1955. pp.&nbsp;582\u2013587.\n* Taylor, John W.R. \"Hunting Jet Provost and BAC 167.\" ''Combat Aircraft of the World from 1909 to the present''. New York: G.P. Putnam's Sons, 1969. {{ISBN|0-425-03633-2}}.\n* Taylor, John W.R., ed. ''Jane's All The World's Aircraft 1971\u201372''. London: Janes's Yearbooks, 1971. {{ISBN|0-354-00094-2}}.\n* Thetford, Owen. ''Aircraft of the Royal Air Force since 1918''. Putnam & Company Limited. {{ISBN|0-370-10056-5}}.\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|BAC Jet Provost}}\n* [http://www.jetprovost.org/ The Jet Provost File: Individual RAF service histories]\n* [http://www.jetprovostheaven.com/ Jet Provost heaven]\n* [http://www.warbirdalley.com/jp.htm Warbird Alley: Jet Provost page]\n\n{{British Aircraft Corporation aircraft}}\n{{Hunting Percival aircraft}}\n{{British military aircraft since World War II}}\n\n[[Category:British Aircraft Corporation aircraft|Jet Provost]]\n[[Category:1950s British military trainer aircraft]]\n[[Category:Hunting Percival aircraft|Jet Provost]]\n[[Category:Single-engined jet aircraft]]\n[[Category:Low-wing aircraft]]\n[[Category:Aircraft first flown in 1954]]\n", "name_user": "Jamie F W", "label": "safe", "comment": "E