{"title_page": "Vaup\u00e9s River", "text_new": "{{Infobox river\n| name               = Vaup\u00e9s River\n| name_native        = \n| name_native_lang   = \n| name_other         = Uaup\u00e9s River\n| name_etymology     = \n<!---------------------- IMAGE & MAP -->\n| image              = \n| image_size         = 300\n| image_caption      = \n| map                = Bcamazonica.jpg\n| map_size           = 300\n| map_caption        = Vaup\u00e9s (Uaup\u00e9s) is in the upper left section\n| pushpin_map        = \n| pushpin_map_size   = 300\n| pushpin_map_caption= \n<!---------------------- LOCATION -->\n| subdivision_type1  = Countries\n| subdivision_name1  = {{hlist|[[Brazil]]|[[Colombia]]}}\n| subdivision_type2  = \n| subdivision_name2  = \n| subdivision_type3  = \n| subdivision_name3  = \n| subdivision_type4  = \n| subdivision_name4  = \n| subdivision_type5  = \n| subdivision_name5  = \n<!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS -->\n| length             = {{convert|1050|km|mi|abbr=on}}<ref name=fao>{{cite book |last1=Ziesler |first1=R. |last2=Ardizzone |first2=G.D. |title=The Inland waters of Latin America |year=1979 |url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/008/ad770b/AD770B05.htm |publisher=[[Food and Agriculture Organization|Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations]] |isbn=92-5-000780-9 |chapter=Amazon River System |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108152358/http://www.fao.org/docrep/008/ad770b/AD770B05.htm |archivedate=8 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref> \n| width_min          = \n| width_avg          = \n| width_max          = \n| depth_min          = \n| depth_avg          = \n| depth_max          = \n| discharge1_location= \n| discharge1_min     = \n| discharge1_avg     = \n| discharge1_max     = \n<!---------------------- BASIN FEATURES -->\n| source1            = \n| source1_location   = [[Guaviare Department]], [[Colombia]]\n| source1_coordinates=   {{coord|2|9|1|N|72|57|13|W|}}  (approximately)\n| source1_elevation  =   360 m (approximately)\n| mouth              = [[Rio Negro (Amazon)|Rio Negro]]\n| mouth_location     = \n| mouth_coordinates  = \n| mouth_elevation    = \n| progression        = \n| river_system       = \n| basin_size         = \n| tributaries_left   = \n| tributaries_right  = \n| custom_label       = \n| custom_data        = \n| extra              = \n}}\n'''Vaup\u00e9s River''' ('''Uaup\u00e9s River''') is a [[tributary]] of the [[Rio Negro (Amazon)|Rio Negro]] in [[South America]]. It rises in the [[Guaviare Department]] of [[Colombia]], flowing east through Guaviare and [[Vaup\u00e9s Department]]s. It forms part of the international border between Colombia and the [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]] state of [[Brazil]].  On the border it merges with the [[Papur\u00ed River]] and becomes known as the Uaup\u00e9s. In 1847 an explorer saw a rapid which hurled its waves {{convert|40|or|50|ft|m|order=flip}} in the air, \"as if great subaqueous explosions were taking place.\"<ref>Discoveries and Explorations, Charles G.D. Roberts, 1905, p.224</ref> The river continues on east through the [[Alto Rio Negro Indigenous Territory]] until it flows into the Rio Negro at [[S\u00e3o Joaquim]], [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]].<ref>{{citation|language=pt|ref={{harvid|Terra Ind\u00edgena Alto Rio Negro \u2013 ISA}}\n |title=Terra Ind\u00edgena Alto Rio Negro|publisher=ISA: Instituto Socioambiental|work=Terras Ind\u00edgenas no Brasil\n |url=https://terrasindigenas.org.br/en/terras-indigenas/4068|accessdate=2017-03-04}}</ref>\nVaup\u00e9s is a [[blackwater river]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of rivers of Amazonas (Brazilian state)|List of rivers of Amazonas]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.zonu.com/imapa/americas/md_amazonas_brazil.pdf Brazilian Ministry of Transport]\n\n{{coord|0.0341833|N|67.2806|W|source:kolossus-dewiki|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vaupes River}}\n[[Category:Rivers of Amazonas (Brazilian state)]]\n[[Category:Rivers of Colombia]]\n[[Category:International rivers of South America]]\n[[Category:Brazil\u2013Colombia border]]\n[[Category:Geography of Vaup\u00e9s Department]]\n[[Category:Geography of Guaviare Department]]\n[[Category:Border rivers]]\n[[Category:Tributaries of the Rio Negro (Amazon)]]\n\n\n{{AmazonasBR-river-stub}}\n{{Colombia-river-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox river\n| name               = Vaup\u00e9s River\n| name_native        = \n| name_native_lang   = \n| name_other         = Uaup\u00e9s River\n| name_etymology     = \n<!---------------------- IMAGE & MAP -->\n| image              = \n| image_size         = 300\n| image_caption      = \n| map                = Bcamazonica.jpg\n| map_size           = 300\n| map_caption        = Vaup\u00e9s (Uaup\u00e9s) is in the upper left section\n| pushpin_map        = \n| pushpin_map_size   = 300\n| pushpin_map_caption= \n<!---------------------- LOCATION -->\n| subdivision_type1  = Countries\n| subdivision_name1  = {{hlist|[[Brazil]]|[[Colombia]]}}\n| subdivision_type2  = \n| subdivision_name2  = \n| subdivision_type3  = \n| subdivision_name3  = \n| subdivision_type4  = \n| subdivision_name4  = \n| subdivision_type5  = \n| subdivision_name5  = \n<!---------------------- PHYSICAL CHARACTERISTICS -->\n| length             = {{convert|1050|km|mi|abbr=on}}<ref name=fao>{{cite book |last1=Ziesler |first1=R. |last2=Ardizzone |first2=G.D. |title=The Inland waters of Latin America |year=1979 |url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/008/ad770b/AD770B05.htm |publisher=[[Food and Agriculture Organization|Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations]] |isbn=92-5-000780-9 |chapter=Amazon River System |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141108152358/http://www.fao.org/docrep/008/ad770b/AD770B05.htm |archivedate=8 November 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref> \n| width_min          = \n| width_avg          = \n| width_max          = \n| depth_min          = \n| depth_avg          = \n| depth_max          = \n| discharge1_location= \n| di